{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"83f2397e-fd05-4335-9654-efad6c6a95e8","content":"In .NET MAUI, you use the **lifecycle events API** in `MauiProgram.cs` via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\npublic static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()\n{\n    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();\n    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();\n\n    builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n    {\n#if ANDROID\n        events.AddAndroid(android => android\n            .OnPause(activity => { /* your code */ })\n            .OnStop(activity => { /* your code */ }));\n#endif\n\n#if IOS\n        events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n            .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* your code */ }));\n#endif\n    });\n\n    return builder.Build();\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#if IOS` preprocessor directives to keep platform code conditional.\n- `AddAndroid` / `AddiOS` expose the native lifecycle events as lambda callbacks.\n- Other events are available too (e.g., `OnResume`, `WillEnterForeground`, `OnCreate`, `WillTerminate`).\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` for the extension methods.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a61d90f9-4c9f-4fa3-9d61-9666851093f1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI development. I can answer this directly without needing to search any codebase.","outputTokens":395,"requestId":"DC0A:7AD2E:A2744:CB237:69F54AE0"},"id":"62c9cfb4-3356-4f8d-b648-6cc2d6fade4c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:52:56.780Z","parentId":"9212ec69-9e24-4c08-a082-5bf1bf7dabef"}
